The paper deals with the problem of program reidentification, which is a critical issue in intrusion detection. The proposed solution involves using a graph neural network to classify the program's identity based on its system behaviors. This work involves the application of machine learning techniques to cybersecurity, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the use of graph neural networks and attention mechanisms indicates that it could also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of real-world enterprise monitoring data, which suggests that it could be classified under cs.SE (Software Engineering) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
